This place is legit.  From its humble beginnings in 1861, this bar has come a long way to become the oldest bar in San Fran.  It was once even a whorehouse for some time!  It probably got its name because it was THE saloon in town when it opened.  A bunch of locals, music lovers, and dive bar aficionados are the primary clientele here.  The beer selection isnt great and one of the two taps is PBR, but you probably wont want to come here for the drinks anyhow.

The oldest bar in San Francisco and the only one that survived the great earthquake of 1906. Authentic saloon where you can listen to the best live blues every night. On Saturdays, payment of an entrance fee ($5, 2013) is required at the time of the concerts, this is not the case the rest of the week.

Very nice place. The average age is quite high despite the youthful attitude of the barmen and customers (that is, old men who squirm while dancing!) Still a typical place, its absolutely worth a visit!

Back in the mid 70s and early 80s this place was my home. Practically received my mail there. Ive been all over the country but this is it. One time I was in a band that was booked to play there. I went to pick up our front man that afternoon. His front door was open and he was asleep on the floor. He hadnt shaved in days. Nobody told the piano player about the gig and the drummer apparently had a better paying gig and sent a substitute. He was the WORST. Dont get me started. I start wheeling the gear in and there is  George Thoroughgood leaning up against the Juke box. We were wretched. George of course left. Lesson: always be prepared, chillun...always be prepared. TJ Ronck.

Wow! We were looking for a place to watch the Niner game while we were staying in Los Angeles for the weekend and boy did we find a gold mine!  The fans here were 110% pro Niners! You like it or you dont.  You want cute little drinks with umbrellas, or some fine cat with a suit and tie, there are places for you.  You want good, no, great music, a solid drink in a water glass, honest conversation, this is the place.  I love this place because its not full of kids and the fifty year old women want to dance.  New Years Eve, this is the place.  Even going solo you can dance all night, and their hubbies do not get jealous.  They are having a great time and want you to have one too.  This place is where you hear real live music, and can have an honestly great time.  Five and a half stars!!!  Hey!  I hear that there are plenty of parking spaces in the Marina tonight.  See ya there.
